(43, 7, 1, 40, 21, 38, 38, 'sought to kill him', 'Connection of Rejection and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the intent to kill Jesus, highlighting the rejection he faced. In John 7:1, the Jews sought to kill him, while in Matthew 21:38, the husbandmen plot to kill the son, indicating a parallel theme of hostility towards God''s messengers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 1, 40, 10, 23, 23, 'sought to kill him', 'Persecution and Fleeing', 'This connection highlights the theme of persecution faced by Jesus and his followers. Both passages emphasize the need to avoid danger and seek safety in the face of threats, as seen in Jesus'' actions and his instructions to his disciples.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 1, 44, 10, 38, 38, 'he would not walk in Jewry', 'Jesus'' Ministry and Opposition', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' active ministry in Galilee while facing opposition from the Jews who sought to kill him. Both passages emphasize Jesus'' actions and the divine support he received, showcasing his mission to heal and do good despite threats.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 1, 42, 13, 31, 33, 'he would not walk in Jewry', 'Jesus'' Danger and Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' awareness of threats to his life. Both passages emphasize the danger he faces, with John noting that ''the Jews sought to kill him'' and Luke mentioning Herod''s intent to kill him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 2, 38, 14, 16, 19, 'feast of tabernacles', 'Feast of Tabernacles Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the feast of tabernacles. John 7:2 mentions the feast being at hand, while Zechariah 14:16-19 describes its future observance by nations, highlighting its importance in worship.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 2, 5, 16, 13, 16, 'feast of tabernacles', 'Connection of Feast of Tabernacles', 'Both passages emphasize the ''feast of tabernacles'' as a significant celebration. John 7:2 mentions the timing of this feast, while Deuteronomy 16:13-16 outlines its observance and importance in the Israelite tradition.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 2, 2, 23, 16, 17, 'feast of tabernacles', 'Connection of Feast References', 'This connection highlights the significance of the ''feast'' mentioned in both passages. John 7:2 refers to the ''feast of tabernacles,'' which aligns with the ''feast of ingathering'' in Exodus 23:16-17, emphasizing the importance of harvest celebrations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 2, 3, 23, 34, 43, 'feast of tabernacles', 'Feast of Tabernacles Connection', 'This connection highlights the observance of the feast of tabernacles in both passages. John 7:2 references the timing of the feast, while Leviticus 23:34-43 provides detailed instructions for its celebration.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 2, 4, 29, 12, 38, 'feast of tabernacles', 'Feast of Tabernacles Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the feast, with John referencing the ''feast of tabernacles'' and Numbers detailing the specific offerings and observances associated with it. This connection highlights the continuity of worship practices in Israel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 2, 11, 8, 2, 2, 'feast of tabernacles', 'Feast Timing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize a significant feast occurring in the seventh month. John 7:2 refers to the feast of tabernacles, which aligns with the timing mentioned in 1 Kings 8:2.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 2, 11, 8, 65, 65, 'feast of tabernacles', 'Feasts in Biblical Context', 'Both passages emphasize significant feasts in Israel''s history. John 7:2 mentions the feast of tabernacles, while 1 Kings 8:65 describes a great feast held by Solomon. This connection highlights the importance of communal worship and celebration in the Jewish tradition.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 3, 40, 12, 46, 46, 'his brethren', 'Family Interaction with Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Jesus'' brethren and their desire to engage with him. In John 7:3, they encourage him to go to Judea, while in Matthew 12:46, they seek to speak with him, highlighting their ongoing involvement in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 3, 43, 7, 5, 5, 'His brethren therefore said unto him', 'Skepticism of Jesus'' Brethren', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the encouragement of Jesus'' brethren to go to Judea and their lack of belief in him. While they urge him to show his works, it is noted that they did not believe in him, emphasizing their skepticism.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 3, 1, 37, 5, 11, NULL, 'Sibling Rivalry and Dreams', 'Both passages emphasize the tension between siblings, as seen in Joseph''s dreams and the disdain from his brethren in Genesis, paralleling the skepticism of Jesus'' brothers in John. This connection highlights the theme of familial conflict arising from perceived superiority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 3, 1, 37, 20, 20, NULL, 'Sibling Betrayal and Ambition', 'This connection highlights the theme of sibling dynamics and ambition. In John 7:3, Jesus'' brothers urge him to display his works, paralleling the brothers in Genesis 37:20 who plot against Joseph''s dreams.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 3, 9, 17, 28, 28, NULL, 'Sibling Reproach and Motivation', 'This connection highlights the theme of sibling reproach, where both passages depict brothers questioning the motivations of a younger sibling. In John 7:3, the brethren urge Jesus to display his works, while in 1 Samuel 17:28, Eliab accuses David of coming to see the battle. Both instances reflect a misunderstanding of the younger sibling''s intentions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 3, 24, 12, 6, 6, 'brethren', 'Betrayal by Brethren', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal by family members. In both passages, the actions and words of brethren are depicted as treacherous or misleading.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 3, 40, 22, 16, 17, 'thy disciples also may see', 'Disciples and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of disciples seeking Jesus'' authority. In John 7:3, the brethren encourage Jesus to show his works to his disciples, while in Matthew 22:16-17, the disciples of the Pharisees approach Jesus to question him about authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 4, 43, 18, 20, 20, 'doeth any thing in secret', 'Openness in Jesus'' Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of openness in Jesus'' actions and teachings. In John 7:4, the call to show oneself openly parallels Jesus'' assertion in John 18:20 that he taught openly and in public spaces.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 4, 20, 18, 1, 2, 'seeketh to be known openly', 'Desire for Public Recognition', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking recognition and understanding. Both passages discuss the desire to be known and the pursuit of wisdom, contrasting the motivations of those who seek to reveal themselves versus those who lack understanding.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 4, 40, 6, 5, 5, 'seeketh to be known openly', 'Public vs. Private Actions', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between actions done in secret and those intended for public recognition. John 7:4 discusses seeking to be known openly, while Matthew 6:5 warns against praying for the sake of being seen by others.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 4, 40, 23, 5, 5, 'shew thyself to the world', 'Public Display of Actions', 'This connection highlights the theme of performing actions for public recognition. Both passages emphasize the desire to be seen by others, whether through open displays or the enlargement of religious symbols.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 4, 42, 6, 45, 45, 'shew thyself to the world', 'Connection of Intent and Action', 'This connection highlights the relationship between outward actions and inner motivations. Both passages emphasize that what is revealed externally reflects the true nature of one''s heart.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
